Input Validation
Input validation ensures that the data received by the program meets the required format and criteria for processing.

Standard Libraries
Standard libraries include prewritten classes and functions in C++ that facilitate various programming operations.

Operator Overloading
Operator Overloading refers to the ability to define custom behavior for operators (like +, -, etc.) in C++, allowing for intuitive use of user-defined types.<SEP>Operator Overloading refers to the ability to define custom behaviors for operators (like >, <, ==) for user-defined classes, enabling intuitive interactions.

String to Rank Function
The String to Rank Function is a function that converts a string representation of a rank (like 'Two', 'Three') to its corresponding Rank enumeration value.

String to Suit Function
The String to Suit Function is a function that converts a string representation of a suit (like 'Hearts', 'Clubs') to its corresponding Suit enumeration value.

Card Class
The Card Class defines the characteristics and behaviors of a playing card, including operations for comparison and input/output.<SEP>The Card Class encapsulates the properties and methods associated with a playing card, including its rank and suit.

Rank Enum
Rank Enum defines the possible ranks of playing cards, from Two to Ace, using integer values for programming.

Suit Enum
Suit Enum defines the possible suits for a playing card, which include Spades, Hearts, Clubs, and Diamonds, also using integers for representation.

istream
istream is a standard input stream in C++ that allows reading data, utilized in the context of reading Card objects from input sources.

ostream
ostream is a standard output stream in C++ that allows writing data, utilized in the context of outputting Card objects to display.<SEP>ostream is part of the C++ standard library used for output streaming, mentioned in the context of printing player names.

Friend Function
A Friend Function in C++ is a function that can access private and protected members of a class, granting special access to manipulate certain data.

Pack Size
Pack Size refers to the constant determining how many cards are in a standard Pack, set to 24 in this implementation.

Player Class

Card Playing Strategy

Game Class

Play Method

Shuffle Method
Shuffle Method refers to a function that randomizes the order of cards within a pack, ensuring fair and unpredictable gameplay.<SEP>The Shuffle Method is an operation within the Pack class that randomizes the order of cards, enhancing gameplay.

string_to_rank

string_to_suit
string_to_suit is a function that converts a string representation of a suit into its enumerated form.

operator<< (Rank)
operator<< (Rank) is an overloaded operator function that allows Rank objects to be output to a stream in a readable format.

operator>>(std::istream&, Rank&)
operator>>(std::istream&, Rank&) is an overloaded operator function that allows reading a Rank from a stream.

operator<<(std::ostream&, Suit)
operator<<(std::ostream&, Suit) is an overloaded operator function that allows Suit objects to be printed in a readable format.

operator>>(std::istream&, Suit&)
operator>>(std::istream&, Suit&) is an overloaded operator function that allows reading a Suit from a stream.
